PROBLEM:¶

Develop a machine learning model which will ingest data like bureau tradelines¶

and demographic metadata of the customers and generate an estimated income.¶

# Fill the missing value for the numerical terms -- mean

bureau_tradelines['PastDueAmount'] = bureau_tradelines['PastDueAmount'].fillna(bureau_tradelines['PastDueAmount'].mean())

bureau_tradelines['SanctionAmount'] = bureau_tradelines['SanctionAmount'].fillna(bureau_tradelines['SanctionAmount'].mean())


bureau_tradelines['InterestRate'] = bureau_tradelines['InterestRate'].fillna(bureau_tradelines['InterestRate'].mean())
bureau_tradelines['InstallmentAmount'] = bureau_tradelines['InstallmentAmount'].fillna(bureau_tradelines['InstallmentAmount'].mean())

from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score, train_test_split
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error

def train(model, X, y):
    # train_the_model
    x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, random_state = 42)
    model.fit(x_train, y_train)
    
    
    #predict the training set
    pred = model.predict(x_test)
    print(pred)
    
    
    # cross-validation
    cv_score = cross_val_score(model, X, y, scoring = 'neg_mean_squared_error', cv=5)
    cv_score = np.abs(np.mean(cv_score))
    cv_score = np.abs(np.mean(cv_score))
    print("Model Reports:")
    errors = abs(y_test - pred)
    print('Mean Absolute Error:', round(np.mean(errors), 2))
    mape=100* (errors/y_test)
    accuracy=100-np.mean(mape/3)
    print('Accuracy of the model:', round(accuracy,2),'%')
    print("MSE:", mean_squared_error(y_test, pred))
    print("CV Score:", cv_score)
